<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>About · Farcaster Lite</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/app.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/header', { active }) %>
  <main class="app-shell single-column prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Production-ready Farcaster client</p>
    <h1>Farcaster Lite</h1>
    <p>A read-only, server-rendered Farcaster client designed to be useful before any secrets exist. Demo mode is first-class; live Neynar credentials can be plugged in later without rewriting the app.</p>
    <div class="check-grid">
      <section><strong>No app-side writes</strong><p>Casts, likes, follows, DMs, payments, auth, and signer custody are intentionally out of scope until explicitly approved.</p></section>
      <section><strong>Provider boundary</strong><p>Routes speak to app-owned provider methods and stable view models, not raw provider JSON.</p></section>
      <section><strong>Server-side keys</strong><p>Provider keys never enter browser JavaScript, rendered HTML, diagnostics, or error states.</p></section>
      <section><strong>Production-shaped UI</strong><p>Feed, search, profile, and thread pages have responsive layouts, empty states, diagnostics, and security headers.</p></section>
    </div>
    <p><a class="more" href="/diagnostics">View production diagnostics</a></p>
  </main>
  <script src="/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
